    "body": "### Problem\n\nmaybe related to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32367\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```sh\n# In a tty, nvim triggers visual bell on xterm-256color.\nnvim --clean -c 'set belloff= visualbell errorbells' -c '!echo -e \"\\a\"'\n\n# In a tty, start tmux without loading any config files on tmp socket.\ntmux -f /dev/null -L tmp\n# nvim does not trigger visual bell on tmux.\nnvim --clean -c 'set belloff= visualbell errorbells' -c '!echo -e \"\\a\"'\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nnvim also triggers visualbell in tmux.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-nightly+5de2ec7\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo. Vim has another issue on beep: https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/17863\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.05 (Warbler) x86_64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix, neovim-nightly-overlay",
