            "body": "```sh\ntmux -f /dev/null -L tmp\ntmux set-option bell-action any\ntmux set-option monitor-bell on\ntmux set-option visual-bell on\n# Vim triggers visual bell as tmux message.\nvim --clean -c 'set belloff= visualbell errorbells' -c '!echo -e \"\\a\"'\n# Neovim triggers no visual bell.\nnvim --clean -c 'set belloff= visualbell errorbells' -c '!echo -e \"\\a\"'\n```\n\nIs the difference on visual bell behavior between vim and neovim as expected?\n\nP.S. The terminal is kitty now.\n\n",
