            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "See https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/17863#issuecomment-3124673369\n\n> I am not sure why you are expecting Vim to cause a visual bell, when Vim switches back to the shell and the shell handles the \"\\a\" completely on its own, that bell should be handled by the shell, not by Vim. I don't think this is a bug right here.\n\nIn Vim a normal bell is triggered, which is shown in tmux as a visual bell. Nvim does not have this behavior, so a real visual bell is used, which doesn't work in tmux.",
