            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I see. `nvim --clean -c 'set belloff= errorbells' -c '!echo -e \"\\a\"'` in tmux works as expected.\n\nSo, two points are involved in the issues:\n\n- Vim and Neovim execute shell commands on different implementations.\n- `tmux` has no ability to snatch `nvim`'s `visualbell` with `tmux`'s `visual-bell` feature.\n\nTo let `tmux`'s `visual-bell` option work with `:!echo -e \"\\a\"`,\n\n- On Vim, `vim`'s `visualbell` option does nothing to do with executing the shell command since Vim spawns another shell to execute `echo -e \"\\a\"`: `vim` just triggers a normal bell by the command regardless of `visualbell` option, and `tmux`'s `visual-bell` option overrides the bell to show a message.\n\n- On Neovim, `nvim`'s `visualbell` option should be disabled when `$TMUX` is set since Neovim executes the command on its own shell implementation to let the bell char to ring on `visualbell`, which `tmux`'s `visual-bell` does not recognize.\n\nIs this understanding correct, so that both of them handle bell as expected, respectively?\n",
